title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) etc. These classes show up prominently in the Open Type dialog. They should be less prominent.
OB: The obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) are displayed prominently in the Open Type dialog.
EB: The obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) should be displayed less prominently in the Open Type dialog.
